Argo AI is in the business of building self-driving technology you can trust. With experienced leaders in the field and collaborative partnerships with some of the world's largest automakers, we're building self-driving technology that is engineered to scale globally and transform mobility for millions. 
 
Talented individuals join our team because they share our purpose to make it safe, easy, and enjoyable for everyone to get around cities. We aspire to impact key industries that move people and goods, from ride hailing to deliveries. 
 
Meet the team: 
 
Argo AI's Autonomous Vehicle System Test Specialists (AVSTSs) are responsible for operating our autonomous vehicles on public roads to enable Argo to continue its testing, monitoring, and development of its Autonomous Vehicle System (AVS). Prior to getting behind the wheel, all AVSTSs undergo a rigorous training program which, among other things, teaches them about the underlying technology of Argo's platforms. More generally, but equally as important, AVSTSs learn Argo's vehicle operating procedures to ensure the safety of the communities in which Argo operates. Once training is complete, AVSTSs are ready to safely take to the road and begin helping our engineers and developers in their continuous efforts to improve Argo's autonomous vehicle software. Be sure to check out our website to learn more about how our AVSTSs play a key role in how we test! 
 
What you'll do: 
 
 Perform the duties of (AVS) operations from both the left seat (driving) and the right seat (co-driving) of Argo's vehicles 
 Undergo a detailed training program that educates and establishes expectations for manual driving fundamentals in autonomous vehicle operation 
 Proactively scan and evaluate dynamic traffic environments while always remaining ready to disengage the autonomous driving function in the event the need arises or safety requires it 
 Deliver clear and concise communications when evaluating AVS performance, documenting both its strengths and areas for improvement, all of which enables Argo's engineers and developers to continuously improve Argo's autonomous driving software 
 Participate in continuing education opportunities as Argo's autonomous driving processes and practices evolve to account for continuing technological changes and development 
 
 Note:  This is a full-time, hourly, non-exempt position 
 
What you'll need to succeed: 
 
 High School Diploma or GED equivalent with two years of employment experience required. Associate or Bachelor's Degree preferred 
 Must have a valid driver's license and the ability to meet and sustain Argo's minimum driving requirements, which Argo evaluates at the hiring stage and periodically thereafter by conducting motor vehicle and criminal record background checks in accordance with applicable law. This position may be subject to additional screenings conducted by third-party partners 
 Desire to be a part of a fast paced, dynamic environment where adaptability and flexibility are essential 
 Ability to monitor software via laptop in a moving vehicle; type proficiently; and communicate in a clear and concise manner 
 Work in a professional and courteous manner at all times 
 Strong interest in technology and software and the ability to adapt to its ever-changing developments and improvements 
 Detail oriented mindset with a focus on safety, honesty, and a strict adherence to Argo's policies and procedures 
 An initial and continued ability to pass a ten-panel drug screen 
 
